#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 PRETORIA - The City of Tshwane is urging residents to have their children vaccinated against measles. A total of 14 lab-confirmed cases have been reported so far. READ: Measles outbreak spreads to 5 provinces: NICD Health MMC Rina Marx says vaccines are available in clinics across the city. She also says outbreak response teams are on standby.